cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and its interaction with deep reinforcement learning. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a novel deep architecture for handling an action space characterized using natural language. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep reinforcement learning to train the proposed model. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to approximate the Q-function. 
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on software engineering specifically, but it may be relevant as the authors implement and evaluate their proposed model on text-based games.
